' A CONST pin must fold to an immediate the compiler can bake into the call frame.
'
' Before plan-50-G, `eval_link_const` ended in `_ => 0`: ANY expression it did not
' recognize silently pinned **0**. A binding pinning a string, or a name, or
' arithmetic got a zero argument with no diagnostic — the third instance of the
' same "default rather than diagnose" mistake as the unvalidated slot ctype
' (plan-50-A) and the nameless link-expr Var (plan-50-I).
LINK "demo" AS demoLink
  FUNC f(n AS Integer) AS Integer
    SYMBOL "demo_f"
    ABI (n CInt32, s CInt32, t CInt32, value OUT CInt32) AS status CInt32
    CONST s = "literal"      ' a string is not an integer immediate
    CONST t = 1 + 1          ' arithmetic is not folded
    RETURN value
    SUCCESS_ON status = 0
  END FUNC
END LINK
